-- South African Police Make Arrests As Shops in Northern Johannesburg Looted
-- Nicky Smith
-- 2010-07-20T06:44:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/south-african-police-arrest-more-than-5-xenophobic-attacks-are-reported.html

          
          
             South African police arrested more
than five people in Kya Sands in northern Johannesburg after
shops were looted between 1:30 a.m. and 3 a.m. today, Katlego
Mogale, a spokeswoman for the police, said in an interview
today.  
 Earlier Talk Radio 702 reported that at least five people
were injured in the area in attacks on foreign immigrants,
citing eyewitnesses.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
